title: Autobiography of Madame Guyon
creator: Jeanne Marie Bouvier de la Motte Guyon
description: LibriVox recording of "The Autobiography of Madame Guyon" by Jeanne Marie Bouvier de la Motte Guyon (1648 - 1717), translated by Thomas Taylor Allen (first published 1897); read by peaceuntoyou, proofed by Heart of Texas, and produced for LibriVox by Karen Merline. Jeanne-Marie Bouvier de la Motte-Guyon (commonly known as Madame Guyon) (April 13, 1648 - June 9, 1717) was a French mystic and one of the key advocates of Quietism. Quietism was considered heretical by the Roman Catholic Church, and she was imprisoned from 1695 to 1703 after publishing a book on the topic, A Short and Easy Method of Prayer. This translation is by Thomas Taylor Allen was first published in 1897. Allen's dates are unknown. (Summary from Wikipedia.)
